1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.837
“No No”s like Ichiro
were sent to Tule Lake.

2
00:00:03.837 --> 00:00:07.424
Tule Lake was a maximum security camp
with explicit orders

3
00:00:07.424 --> 00:00:12.762
to the guards to shoot if they found
any of the incarcerated suspicious.

4
00:00:12.762 --> 00:00:19.978
Shoichi James Okamoto was
one of 18,700 incarcerated at Tule Lake.

5
00:00:19.978 --> 00:00:23.106
On May 24th 1944,

6
00:00:23.106 --> 00:00:27.527
Okamoto, while driving a construction
truck back and forth between the camp

7
00:00:27.527 --> 00:00:32.157
and the worksite outside
a camp, was stopped by a center gate sentry,

8
00:00:32.157 --> 00:00:36.661
demanding that Okamoto
step out of his truck and show his pass.

9
00:00:36.661 --> 00:00:41.708
Okamoto stepped out of the cab
but refused to show his pass.

10
00:00:41.708 --> 00:00:45.754
Where upon the sentry
struck him on the shoulder with his rifle.

11
00:00:45.754 --> 00:00:52.385
The two exchanged words
in the sentry shot Okamoto.

12
00:00:52.761 --> 00:00:55.472
The next day he died.

13
00:00:55.472 --> 00:00:58.016
He was 30 years old.

14
00:00:58.016 --> 00:01:03.396
At the court martial trial,
the sentry was acquitted of the homicide

15
00:01:03.396 --> 00:01:09.569
and only charged $1
for the cost of the bullet.

